@t{Declt} can be used be used when you need to generate API reference for third-party libraries
as @url{https://quickref.common-lisp.net/, Quickref} does for all Quicklisp libraries.

Ability to generate docs in different formats also might be interesting.

But the lack of markup support for docstrings and cross-reference helpers along with limited ability
to create free form documentation chapters makes @t{Declt} useless for documenting
@url{https://40ants.com, 40Ants projects}.
